main event: A witness observed an unidentified illuminated object with a revolving motion over Wright-Patterson AFB, Ohio on October 5, 1960.
interesting points: The object appeared to have a trailing cut off and disappeared into the dim night sky.
The object was described as illuminated and revolving.
The witness stated the stars appeared yellow in color and there was no sound associated with the object.
The sighting lasted for approximately 15 minutes.
The conclusion of the report was that the sighting provided insufficient information for evaluation.
